---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageMeta from '@/components/PageMeta.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Member implementations"
  description="What each OPDA member firm has built or shipped that's public-facing — by bounded context."
>
<PageMeta category="Adoption" variant="brand" updated="Updated 2026-05-14" />

      <h1>Member implementations</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Each OPDA member firm is at a different point on the
        <a href="/adoption/adoption-overview">adoption spectrum</a>. The table below
        captures what's <em>publicly visible</em> from each — the products, pilots
        and references that you can verify from outside.
      </p>

      <div class="callout callout--note">
        <div class="callout__label">Scope</div>
        <p>
          Coverage is best-effort and may lag behind what members are building. For the
          authoritative roster see <a href="/governance/opda-members">OPDA member firms</a>;
          this page focuses on <em>what they've done</em>, not who they are.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-top: var(--space-2);">
          Some evidence below is sourced from <code>propdata.org.uk</code> — a legacy developer site that carries
          OPDA copyright but was <strong>not authored or approved by OPDA</strong> (OPDA has no editing access).
          Such citations are recorded for reference, not as OPDA-verified membership statements.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="estateAgency">Estate Agency</h2>

      <table>
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width:24%"><col style="width:48%"><col style="width:28%">
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Member</th><th>What's shipped</th><th>Evidence</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Moverly</strong> <em>(former member)</em></td>
            <td>Smart Property Pack product. Tightly coupled to the PDTF schema set; produced BASPI v5 + NTS2 conforming data. A founding member and key author of the original schema, Moverly has since left OPDA — no longer part of its membership, accreditation/approvals, or the sandbox.</td>
            <td>Smart Data Challenge prize entry (see <a href="/adoption/smart-data-challenge">SDC page</a>). Vimeo briefing.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Coadjute</strong></td>
            <td>Property transaction network — distributed-ledger plumbing for sale-progression workflows.</td>
            <td>propdata.org.uk membership; referenced in DPMSG materials.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>PEXA</strong></td>
            <td>E-conveyancing network operator (originally Australian; UK arm).</td>
            <td>Founding member; cited as orchestration provider in the DPMSG Spring 2025 report.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>OnTheMarket</strong></td>
            <td>Property portal; PDTF-aware listing data ingestion.</td>
            <td>Founding member; portal listings include BASPI-aligned material info.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Homely</strong></td>
            <td>Property platform; consumer-facing property packs.</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Connells</strong> <em>(association)</em></td>
            <td>"Digital Sale Ready" programme — branch network using PDTF-aligned data capture.</td>
            <td>Cited on propdata.org.uk. Sale-progression case study (industry press).</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="conveyancing">Conveyancing</h2>

      <table>
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width:24%"><col style="width:48%"><col style="width:28%">
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Member</th><th>What's shipped</th><th>Evidence</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>LMS</strong></td>
            <td>Managed conveyancing services firm. TA6/TA10/LPE1 data exchange with member panels.</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Smoove · Movera · Movemnt</strong> <em>(association)</em></td>
            <td>Conveyancing comparison and orchestration platforms.</td>
            <td>Association members; integrate with PDTF-aligned conveyancers.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="mortgageLending">Mortgage Lending</h2>

      <table>
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width:24%"><col style="width:48%"><col style="width:28%">
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Member</th><th>What's shipped</th><th>Evidence</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>United Trust Bank (UTB)</strong></td>
            <td>Founding lender. Inputs FME1-aligned data via OMS integration.</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>OMS</strong></td>
            <td>Mortgage technology platform supporting FME1 data flows.</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>HSBC UK · Nationwide · NatWest · Lloyds Banking Group · Santander</strong> <em>(association)</em></td>
            <td>Major UK lenders. Engaged via UK Finance representation on DPMSG.</td>
            <td>UK Finance + BSA as DPMSG founding members.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Finova · Phoebus · MAB · L&amp;C · Lenderhive</strong> <em>(association)</em></td>
            <td>Lender-tech and intermediary platforms.</td>
            <td>Association membership.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="propertyData">Property Data Services</h2>

      <table>
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width:24%"><col style="width:48%"><col style="width:28%">
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Member</th><th>What's shipped</th><th>Evidence</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Sprift</strong></td>
            <td>Property data aggregator. Surfaces local-authority &amp; HMLR-sourced data via PDTF-shaped APIs.</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Groundsure</strong></td>
            <td>Search products (CON29DW-aligned drainage &amp; water).</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>TM Group</strong></td>
            <td>Conveyancing search aggregator.</td>
            <td>Founding member.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Kotini · Inventory Base</strong></td>
            <td>Inventory and check-in data providers.</td>
            <td>Founding members.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Hometrack · Experian · Credas</strong> <em>(association)</em></td>
            <td>AVM, identity, and adjacent data services.</td>
            <td>Association members.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 id="propertyTech">Property Tech (orchestration)</h2>

      <table>
        <colgroup>
          <col style="width:24%"><col style="width:48%"><col style="width:28%">
        </colgroup>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Member</th><th>What's shipped</th><th>Evidence</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Moverly</strong> <em>(former member)</em></td>
            <td>(also in Estate Agency) — orchestration product on the same stack.</td>
            <td>SDC prize (2025). Former member — no longer in OPDA's membership/accreditation.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td><strong>Coadjute</strong> &amp; <strong>PEXA</strong></td>
            <td>(also in Estate Agency) — system-to-system orchestration.</td>
            <td>Founding members.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="callout callout--warn">
        <div class="callout__label">Notable absence</div>
        <p>
          <strong>Surveying / Valuation has no founding OPDA member.</strong>
          PIQ is in the schema set but no implementing firm has put their name
          publicly to the section. Hometrack (AVM-adjacent) is the closest in the
          association membership. See <a href="/modelling/bounded-contexts#primaryIndustries">Bounded contexts</a> for the gap analysis.
        </p>
      </div>
</Layout>
